  "id": "019cface-e2f0-78c0-8b17-4da32cee859a",
  "content": "## 01_extract_frames.py — Implementation Complete\n\nPhase 1 script implemented at `scripts/01_extract_frames.py`. Key details:\n\n### How it works\n1. Resolves workspace root via `$CORVIA_WORKSPACE` env var or walking up from script location\n2. Loads `repos/dorea/config.yaml` for `footage_raw`, `footage_flat`, and `working_dir` paths\n3. Scans `footage/raw/{date}/` and `footage/flat/{date}/` for video files (.mp4, .MP4, .mov, .MOV, .avi, .AVI)\n4. For each clip, runs: `ffmpeg -i {clip} -vf fps=0.5,scale=1280:-1 -q:v 5 working/keyframes/{clip_id}/frame_%06d.jpg`\n5. clip_id = filename stem (e.g., `DJI_0042.MP4` → `DJI_0042`)\n\n### CLI\n`python 01_extract_frames.py --date YYYY-MM-DD [--verbose]`\n\n### Error handling\n- Missing footage dirs → exit 1 with clear message\n- No video files found → exit 1\n- ffmpeg failure on individual clip → log error, continue with remaining clips\n- All clips failed → exit 1\n\n### Dependencies\n- ffmpeg (system), PyYAML (pip), Python stdlib only\n- No GPU required (CPU-only ffmpeg)\n\n### Output\n- `working/keyframes/{clip_id}/frame_NNNNNN.jpg` — 1280px wide, JPEG quality ~85%, sequential numbering from 000001",
